### [Visual Studio Code](https://code.visualstudio.com/)

#### Install using Command Palette

1.  Go to `View -> Command Palette` or press `Ctrl+Shift+P`
2.  Then enter `Install Extension`
3.  Write `Wednesday Official`
4.  Select it or press Enter to install

#### Install using Git

If you are a git user, you can install the theme and keep up to date by cloning the repo:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/djoezeke/Wednesday.git ~/.vscode/extensions/theme-wednesday
cd ~/.vscode/extensions/theme-wednesday
npm install
npm run build
```

#### Activating theme

Run Visual Studio Code. The Wednesday Syntax Theme will be available from `File -> Preferences -> Color Theme` dropdown menu.
